1.   A supervised, inexpensive lodging place for travelers, especially young travelers. 2.   An inn; a hotel. 1.  a building providing overnight accommodation, as for the homeless, etc 2.   (Other Non-sporting Hobbies) See  youth hostel 3.  Brit  a supervised lodging house for nurses, workers, etc 4.  archaic  another word for  hostelry    1.   an inexpensive, supervised lodging place for young travelers.     2.   an inn.     3.   to travel, lodging each night at a hostel. 